comments:
-It's a great amount of work outside of class (shooting, editing etc), but it's rewarding in the end, as you get to complete your own short film, and you are encouraged to step outside of your confort zone and make steps towards professional documentary film-making;
-the fact that the class is three hours, twice a week, is often necessary, but sometimes makes it unbearable; 
-the instructors are great and extremely accessible and helpful all the time.
